<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-948-516  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 948 516.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>3D  Oct 1989 n18 p34(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Scanners - a clearer picture.(Includes related articles onscanning tips and the International Scanning Technology Users Assnas well as a scanners buyers guide) (buyers guide)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Scanners are experiencing a resurgence in popularity due to recentdevelopments in scanner technology, dramatically lower prices, anda wider range of low-end products.andP;  Additionally, emergingstandards have resulted in the development of image enhancementpackages that let users retouch and manipulate poorly scannedimages.andP;  Video scanners give the highest quality output, but areexpensive and require practice to use well.andP;  Flatbed scanners aremore popular, and are as easy as photocopiers to use.andP;  Hand-heldscanners give the poorest resolution, but cost as little as 200pounds sterling.andP;  Most scanners use dithering techniques forproducing printing images, and TIFF (Tagged Image File Format),although greedy on disk space and memory, is the most popularscanned image file format.andP;  Color scanners are now available forabout 2,000 pounds sterling, and total systems for large formatscanning are now available for about 9,000 pounds sterling.andP;  AScanners Buyers Guide, listing manufacturers and productspecifications, is included.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ScanningProductsFunctional CapabilitiesColorMarketTechnologyEnd UsersStandardsPrice.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographtable.andO;Caption:   Scanners buyers guide. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>